author: Digital Foundry
description:
Content sponsored by Nvidia. 2005: a pivotal year in gaming, with the arrival of a new generation of titles, enabled on PC with the arrival of Shader Model 3, supported by Nvidia's cutting-edge GeForce 7800 GTX. 20 years on, Alex powers up a period-appropriate PC equipped with the 7800 GTX, showcasing how the hardware delivered more performance and new features over its predecessors in a range of classic PC titles. 

00:00:00 Introduction
00:02:19 The 7800 GTX Legacy
00:05:01 What did the 7800 GTX bring to the table in 2005?
00:09:23 Battlefield 2 vs 7800 GTX
00:11:53 F.E.A.R. vs 7800 GTX
00:15:39 Age of Empires 3 vs 7800 GTX
00:17:44 Splinter Cell: Chaos Theory vs 7800 GTX
00:19:51 SLI and Conclusion
title: DF Retro: Nvidia GeForce 7800 GTX - 20th Anniversary Retrospective - A Generational Leap [Sponsored]
